comments: Vucevic (CHI) absorbs the contact from Allen (CLE) to his forearm and does not deliver contact during the screen.
Mitchell (CLE) legally contests Dosunmu's (CHI) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Okoro (CLE) faces up with Vucevic (CHI) and impedes his ability to pursue the rebound.
LaVine (CHI) legally contests Mitchell's (CLE) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Williams (CHI) establishes himself in Allen's (CLE) path and does not deliver contact.
Allen (CLE) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Vucevic (CHI) places his bent forearm to Osman's (CLE) backside and marginal contact occurs as Osman's momentum carries him towards the basket.
DeRozan (CHI) makes contact with Love's (CLE) forearm prior to making any contact with the ball.
Vucevic (CHI) brings his hands toward LeVert (CLE) and marginal contact occurs as Vucevic (CHI) releases away to roll.
Love (CLE) briefly grasps Vucevic's (CHI) arm and marginal contact occurs as Vucevic back taps the ball during rbeounding.
Vucevic (CHI) is already in LeVert's (CLE) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
LeVert (CLE) brings his hand slightly forward towards DeRozan's (CHI) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Mitchell (CLE) brushes LaVine's (CHI) arm and marginal contact occurs as LaVine starts his drive.
DeRozan (CHI) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Osman (CLE) legally contests Vucevic's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
Williams (CHI) and LeVert (CLE) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Allen (CLE) is firming up in Dosunmu's (CHI) path and does not deliver contact during the pick.
Vucevic (CHI) is moving alongside Mitchell's (CLE) path and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Dosunmu (CHI) is moving alongside Mitchell's (CLE) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.

As Williams (CHI) contests Allen's (CLE) shot near the rim, his forearm makes some contact with Allen's head.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Love (CLE) commits a take foul on Dosunmu (CHI) . The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Allen (CLE) establishes himself in Dosunmu's (CHI) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
DeRozan (CHI) is moving alongside Mitchell's (CLE) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Allen (CLE) lifts and re-plants his pivot foot without releasing the ball.
Vucevic (CHI) places a stayed hand to Allen's (CLE) back and immediately removes his hand as Allen begins his upward shooting motion.
Mitchell (CLE) commits a take foul on White (CHI). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Dosunmu (CHI) commits a take foul on Mitchell (CLE).  The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Drummond (CHI) briefly grasps Lopez's (CLE) arm and marginal contact occurs during rebounding.
Mitchell (CLE) steps over the plane of the free throw line before the ball touches the basket ring.
DeRozan (CHI) applies his forearm to Mitchell's (CLE) upper body and marginal contact occurs as Mitchell's momentum carries him towards DeRozan.
Allen (CLE) engages and disengages with White (CHI) and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
LeVert (CLE) briefly grasps Vucevic's (CHI) arm before immediately releasing his arm off ball.
White (CHI) is already in Allen's (CLE) path and does not deliver contact.
LaVine (CHI) engages with LeVert (CLE) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as LaVine (CHI) releases away.
LeVert (CLE) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
